    <div class="row g-4 m-0 p-0">
      <h3 class="display-5 text-center">Glosary</h3>
      
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card shadow-sm">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="card-title">Attributes</h3>
            <p class="text-center">
              "Digimon attributes (Data, Vaccine, Virus, Free, Variable) categorize file types and influence interactions. Vaccine beats Virus, Virus beats Data, Data beats Vaccine, like rock-paper-scissors. Attributes can affect Digimon appearance and attacks. Variable adapts to the opponent. While same-attribute Digimon are generally friendly, alignment isn't fixed. The attribute system, originally a virtual pet mechanic, remains relevant, especially in the card game."
            </p>
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center flex-wrap">
              {{#each attributes as |attribute|}}
                <span class="badge bg-success m-2"
                  data-bs-toggle="tooltip" 
                  data-bs-title="{{attribute.description}}"
                >
                {{attribute.name}}
                </span>
              {{/each}}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card shadow-sm">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="card-title">Levels</h3>
            <p class="text-center">
              An Evolution Stage, also referred to as Level and Generation, is the level of development a Digimon is at.
            </p>
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center flex-wrap">
              {{#each levels as |level|}}
                <span class="badge bg-success m-2" 
                  data-bs-toggle="tooltip" 
                  data-bs-title="{{level.description}}"
                >
                  {{level.name}}
                </span>
              {{/each}}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
